  "text": "Classically, severe cases of mitral stenosis with suitable valve morphology were managed by surgery i.e. CMC. However, open mitral commissurotomy (OMC) is being used for suitable, complicated cases, like before. On the other hand, for mitral valve replacement, some bioprostheses were used initially, which were later replaced by metallo-prostheses. Initial ball-and-case metallic valves are out of use now-a-days, majority of the prostheses used today are bileaflet valves. In the recent years, primary angioplasty is being performed in Government [CITATION_1] , as well as, in private [CITATION_2] centers.",
